article.headline: Missouri St. 65, Indiana St. 44
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Dale Lamberth came off the bench to score 15 points and lead Missouri State to a 65-44 win over Indiana State on Tuesday. Missouri State (10-8, 3-3 Missouri Valley) had the game in hand by halftime, taking a 32-12 into the break thanks to poor Indiana State shooting. After Indiana State (9-7, 4-2) closed the gap to 36-22 with 16:18 left on a 3-pointer by Gabe Moore, the Bears responded with a 13-2 run to extend to lead to 49-24 with 10:38 remaining. Spencer Laurie had 12 points for Missouri State, which shot 51 percent from the field and 43 percent from the 3-point line. Harry Marshall led Indiana State with nine points.
